Yes Newcastle Coal 380USD/T +8.76%moved towards the $400 per tonne mark  more than 150% above last year's level again  on prospects of continued robust demand and tight supplies. And above-average demand from Europe on fears of a shortage of natural gas for power generation coupled with skyrocketing imports of thermal coal from India  as electricity demand increased because of a heatwave and a pickup in economic activity  have been pushing prices higher. On top of that  a seasonal upturn in coal-fired generation during the winter reinforced this view of solid global demand.
